124
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:30,740
How did you do?

125
00:07:30,740 --> 00:07:33,130
Could you hear the prices correctly?

126
00:07:33,130 --> 00:07:38,720
Understanding numbers, especially when people
read the numbers in this conversational way,

127
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:44,360
can really help you when you’re shopping
in an English-speaking country.

128
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:52,800
Next, let’s look at another common task
when you’re shopping: arranging delivery.

129
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,800
Yes, can I help?

130
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,880
Well…

131
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,800
I’ve just bought this TV…

132
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,180
Yes?

133
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:00,200
And…

134
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,660
It’s much bigger than I expected.

135
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:05,400
I’m not sure it’ll fit in my car.

136
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:07,500
Do you offer a delivery service?

137
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,900
Yes, of course!

138
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:11,780
I’m surprised they didn’t mention it to
you when you paid.

139
00:08:11,780 --> 00:08:13,200
That’s great!

140
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,700
So, what do I do?

141
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,000
Can I take your receipt, please?

142
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Of course; here you are.

143
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,500
Let me see…

144
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,700
The earliest we could deliver it would be
next Wednesday.

145
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:25,000
Does that work for you?

146
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,100
I’m at work during the week.

147
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,800
Do you deliver at weekends?

148
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:32,800
We can deliver on Saturdays, but there’s
a four-pound charge.

149
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:33,800
That’s fine.

150
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:36,140
So, next Saturday, the 29th?

151
00:08:36,180 --> 00:08:38,840
That works, but what time will it be?

152
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,580
We deliver between ten AM and four PM.

153
00:08:41,589 --> 00:08:44,089
You can’t give me a more specific time than
that?

154
00:08:44,089 --> 00:08:45,740
I’m afraid not.

155
00:08:45,740 --> 00:08:48,050
All of our delivery slots are six hours.

156
00:08:48,050 --> 00:08:50,290
I guess I’ll have to take it, then.

157
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:55,140
OK, so you just need to pay the weekend delivery
charge, and then we can set everything up

158
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:55,960
for you.

159
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,120
Can I pay by card?

160
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:59,220
Of course.

161
00:08:59,230 --> 00:09:04,050
Of course, it’s more common nowadays to
order things online and have them delivered

162
00:09:04,050 --> 00:09:06,050
to your home.

163
00:09:06,050 --> 00:09:13,459
But maybe you want to see your new TV screen
in action, try out your new sofa, or check

164
00:09:13,459 --> 00:09:17,140
that your new table will match your living
room.

165
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:22,110
In this case, you might need to arrange a
delivery in the shop.

166
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:27,000
To do this, you could ask: ‘Can I have this
delivered?’

167
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,620
‘Do you offer a delivery service?’

168
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:34,240
‘Can you deliver this to my house?’

169
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:39,199
Quick quiz: you heard one of these three questions
in the dialogue.

170
00:09:39,199 --> 00:09:41,779
Which one?

171
00:09:41,779 --> 00:09:43,420
You heard the second one.

172
00:09:43,420 --> 00:09:46,259
However, they all have the same meaning.

173
00:09:46,259 --> 00:09:49,029
You can use any of them!

174
00:09:49,029 --> 00:09:54,129
You might also need to ask more specific questions
about the delivery, like: ‘Do you deliver

175
00:09:54,129 --> 00:09:56,100
at weekends?’

176
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:59,020
‘What time will it be?’

177
00:09:59,020 --> 00:10:03,300
‘Do you have any slots available next Friday?’

178
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:07,480
‘Does weekend delivery cost extra?’

179
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:11,310
What does that word ‘slot’ mean?

180
00:10:11,310 --> 00:10:14,860
A ‘slot’ is a time period when something
can happen.

181
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:21,310
Often, a shop or company will give you a delivery
slot, for example from nine in the morning

182
00:10:21,310 --> 00:10:23,829
to two in the afternoon.

183
00:10:23,829 --> 00:10:29,480
You know your delivery will arrive sometime
in that window, but you don’t know exactly

184
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,880
when.

185
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:37,680
Now, you can ask about availability, ask about
prices, and arrange a delivery if you need

186
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,600
it.

187
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:46,900
But, what if you have a problem with something
you bought in a shop?

188
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:48,660
Hello, what can I do for you?

189
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:53,200
Hi, yes, I bought these jeans last week, and
I’d like to return them.

190
00:10:53,209 --> 00:10:54,209
Do you have your receipt?

191
00:10:54,209 --> 00:10:56,310
Yes, here you are.

192
00:10:56,310 --> 00:10:58,180
Was anything wrong with the jeans?

193
00:10:58,180 --> 00:11:01,029
No, no problem, they’re just the wrong size.

194
00:11:01,029 --> 00:11:02,149
They’re too small.

195
00:11:02,149 --> 00:11:04,779
Would you like to exchange them for a larger
size?

196
00:11:04,779 --> 00:11:06,850
I can check if we have them in stock.

197
00:11:06,850 --> 00:11:07,850
No, thank you.

198
00:11:07,850 --> 00:11:10,939
I decided that I don’t like the style so
much, either.

199
00:11:10,939 --> 00:11:12,790
Is it possible to get a refund?

200
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:14,029
Of course.

201
00:11:14,029 --> 00:11:15,620
Do you have the card you paid with?

202
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:17,160
Can’t I get cash?

203
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:21,620
I’m sorry, but we can only issue a refund
to the card you paid with.

204
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:25,499
Alternatively, we can offer you gift vouchers
for the same amount.

205
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,380
Fine, put it on the card, then.

206
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:29,420
No problem.

207
00:11:29,420 --> 00:11:34,260
At the start of the dialogue, you heard: ‘I
bought these jeans last week, and I’d like

208
00:11:34,269 --> 00:11:36,329
to return them.’

209
00:11:36,329 --> 00:11:39,499
‘Return’ could mean different things.

210
00:11:39,499 --> 00:11:44,880
Generally, you can *replace* something, meaning
you get another of the same thing.

211
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:50,500
For example, if you buy a new phone, and it
doesn’t work when you take it out of the

212
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:57,310
box, you might ask to replace it—you get
a new version of the same phone.

213
00:11:57,310 --> 00:12:02,660
You could also ask to *exchange* the product
you bought, meaning you give back the one

214
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:06,320
you bought, and take a different one, instead.

215
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:11,600
Maybe you bought some clothes, but then you
decided they don’t look as good as you hoped,

216
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:15,060
and you want to take something different.

217
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:20,240
Finally, you can ask for a refund, and get
your money back.

218
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:24,670
When you take something back to a shop, you
might hear questions like: ‘Do you have

219
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:26,960
your receipt?’

220
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:33,040
‘Was anything wrong with …?’
‘Would you like to exchange it for something

221
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,900
else?’

